cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image-to-image translation. The use of GANs also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper's focus on collaboration between GANs and its ability to remove large objects and translate between domains that require large shape modifications suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of multiple optional and diverse images also suggests that it could belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on challenging applications and commonly-used datasets suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
